paragraphs.text: %md ## OML4Py Feature Extraction: Singular Value Decomposition The Oracle Machine Learning for Python function *oml.svd* creates a model that uses the Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) algorithm for feature extraction. In this notebook, we demonstrate how to use the in-database SVD decomposion for feature extraction using the Breast Cancer dataset from the University of Wisconsin. We show that Principal Component Analysis (PCA) can be achieved using SVD results. All processing occurs inside Oracle Autonomous Database. #### Breast Cancer from the University of Wisconsin dataset (1992) - Features are computed from a digitized image of a fine needle aspirate (FNA) of a breast mass. - The original dataset contains 31 attributes, including the TARGET attribute that is '1' for malignant tumors, and '0' for benign tumors. msg.data:
OML4Py Feature Extraction: Singular Value Decomposition

The Oracle Machine Learning for Python function oml.svd creates a model that uses the Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) algorithm for feature extraction.

In this notebook, we demonstrate how to use the in-database SVD decomposion for feature extraction using the Breast Cancer dataset from the University of Wisconsin.
We show that Principal Component Analysis (PCA) can be achieved using SVD results. All processing occurs inside Oracle Autonomous Database.

Breast Cancer from the University of Wisconsin dataset (1992)

  • Features are computed from a digitized image of a fine needle aspirate (FNA) of a breast mass.
  • The original dataset contains 31 attributes, including the TARGET attribute that is '1' for malignant tumors, and '0' for benign tumors.

paragraphs.title: Initialize the environment
paragraphs.text:
%python

import oml

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

import pandas as pd

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.style.use('seaborn')

paragraphs.title: Load data from Scikit-Learn
paragraphs.text:
%python

from sklearn import datasets
bc = datasets.load_breast_cancer()

bc_data = bc.data.astype(float)
X = pd.DataFrame(bc_data, columns = bc.feature_names)
y = pd.DataFrame(bc.target, columns = ['TARGET'])

paragraphs.title: Push the dataset to Oracle Database
paragraphs.text:
%python

try:
    oml.drop(table='BREASTCANCER')
except:
    pass

BREASTCANCER = oml.create(pd.concat([X, y], axis=1), table = 'BREASTCANCER')
print("Shape:",BREASTCANCER.shape)

paragraphs.title: Build an SVD model
paragraphs.text:
%python

try:
    oml.drop(model='SVD_TEST_MODEL')
except:
    pass

# Create an oml SVD model object
svd_mod = oml.svd(ODMS_DETAILS = 'ODMS_ENABLE',
                  PREP_AUTO = 'ON',
                  SVDS_SCORING_MODE = 'SVDS_SCORING_PCA')
                  
# Fit the model according to all data
svd_mod = svd_mod.fit(BREASTCANCER, model_name='SVD_TEST_MODEL')

paragraphs.title: Show the model details
paragraphs.text:
%python

svd_mod

paragraphs.title: The D matrix contains the singular values
paragraphs.text:
%python

svd_d = svd_mod.d[(svd_mod.d['VALUE'].round(0)>0),:].round(decimals=0).pull()
svd_d['Percent_of_Total'] = 100*(svd_d['VALUE']/svd_d['VALUE'].sum())
z.show(svd_d.round(4))

paragraphs.title: Perform dimensionality reduction
paragraphs.text:
%python

# Return the selection of the top 3 features that represent 97% of variability
z.show(svd_mod.transform(BREASTCANCER, 
       supplemental_cols = BREASTCANCER[:, ['TARGET']], topN = 3).sort_values(by = ['TARGET', 'TOP_1', 'TOP_1_VAL']))

                       compare_cols = "mean radius", supplemental_cols = ["TARGET"]))

### Using the SVD Model for Prediction of Principal Component projections

msg.data: Using the SVD Model for Prediction of Principal Component projections

paragraphs.title: Drop the table if it exists
Create a table that contains the projections
paragraphs.text:
%sql

CREATE TABLE BC_PCA_PROJECTIONS AS 
SELECT "worst area", "mean area", "area error", 
       FEATURE_VALUE(SVD_TEST_MODEL, 1 USING *) PCA_PROJ1,
       FEATURE_VALUE(SVD_TEST_MODEL, 2 USING *) PCA_PROJ2,
       FEATURE_VALUE(SVD_TEST_MODEL, 3 USING *) PCA_PROJ3

FROM BREASTCANCER
ORDER BY 1, 2

paragraphs.title: Look at the PCA projections
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select * from BC_PCA_PROJECTIONS

paragraphs.title: Original data - top 3 attributes
paragraphs.text:
%python

# Bring the data locally for plotting

BC_PCA_PROJECTIONS = oml.sync(table = "BC_PCA_PROJECTIONS")
bc_proj_local = BC_PCA_PROJECTIONS.pull()

from pandas.plotting import scatter_matrix

scattermat = scatter_matrix(
    bc_proj_local[['worst area','mean area', 'area error']],
    figsize  = [30, 30],
    marker   = ".",
    s        = 400,
    diagonal = "kde",
    color='red'
)

for ax in scattermat.ravel():
    ax.set_xlabel(ax.get_xlabel(), fontsize = 24, rotation = 90)
    ax.set_ylabel(ax.get_ylabel(), fontsize = 24, rotation = 90)
    
_=plt.show()

paragraphs.title: SVD-PCA projections - top 3 Principal Components
paragraphs.text:
%python

scattermat = scatter_matrix(
    bc_proj_local[['PCA_PROJ1','PCA_PROJ2', 'PCA_PROJ3']],
    figsize  = [30, 30],
    marker   = ".",
    s        = 400,
    diagonal = "kde",
    color='red'
)

for ax in scattermat.ravel():
    ax.set_xlabel(ax.get_xlabel(), fontsize = 24, rotation = 90)
    ax.set_ylabel(ax.get_ylabel(), fontsize = 24, rotation = 90)
    
_=plt.show()

Help on class svd in module oml.algo.svd:

class svd(oml.algo.model.odmModel)
 |  svd(model_name=None, model_owner=None, **params)
 |  
 |  In-database `Singular Value Decomposition <https://www.oracle.com/machine-learning/singular-value-decomposition>`_ Model
 |  
 |  Builds a Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) Model that can be used for feature 
 |  extraction. SVD provides orthogonal linear transformations that capture the 
 |  underlying variance of the data by decomposing a rectangular matrix into three 
 |  matrixes: U, D, and V. Matrix D is a diagonal matrix and its singular values 
 |  reflect the amount of data variance captured by the bases. Columns of matrix V 
 |  contain the right singular vectors and columns of matrix U contain the left singular
 |  vectors.
 |  
 |  :Attributes:
 |  
 |      **features** : oml.DataFrame
 |      
 |        Features extracted by the fitted model including feature id and associated coefficient.
 |        It includes the following components:
 |            
 |            - feature_id: The ID of a feature in the model
 |            - attribute_name: The attribute name
 |            - attribute_value: The attribute value
 |            - value: The matrix entry value
 |            
 |      **u** : oml.DataFrame
 |      
 |        A dataframe whose columns contain the left singular vectors.
 |        The column name is the corresponding feature id.
 |        
 |      **v** : oml.DataFrame
 |      
 |        A dataframe whose columns contain the right singular vectors.
 |        The column name is the corresponding feature id.
 |        
 |      **d** : oml.DataFrame
 |      
 |        A dataframe containing the singular values of the input data.
 |        It includes the following components:
 |            
 |            - feature_id: The ID of a feature in the model
 |            - value: The singular values of the input data
